OL,3,C'Destroy ninja swords' say police as
OL,4,C66 handed in just last month
OL,6,FIt was already a criminal offence to
OL,7,Fcarry the weapons in public.
OL,9,FNinja swords are defined as having a
OL,10,Fblade between 14 and 24 inches, a
OL,11,Fstraight cutting edge, and a tanto-
OL,12,Fstyle point (angled tip).
OL,14,FBreaking the law could lead to a
OL,15,Fprison sentence of up to six months,
OL,16,Fpotentially increasing to two years
OL,17,Funder new measures.
OL,19,FCarrying a weapon in public already
OL,20,Fcarries a penalty of up to four years
OL,21,Fin prison.
