OL,3,C'Destroy ninja swords' say police as
OL,4,C66 handed in just last month
OL,6,FChief Inspector James Kitchen has
OL,7,Fencouraged people to hand over ot
OL,8,Fdestroy the weapons that are now
OL,9,Fillegal.
OL,11,F"We have been very pleased with the
OL,12,Fresponse from the public to the July
OL,13,Famnesty and want others who own
OL,14,Fweapons that are now illegal to hand
OL,15,Fthen in or ethically destroy them ASAP.
OL,17,F"The ban on owning ninja swords was a
OL,18,Fvery welcome change to the law which
OL,19,Fgives us a much better ability to
OL,20,Flimit the availability of these
OL,21,Fdangerous weapons.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G3/4
